1
00:00:11,731 --> 00:00:13,940
Day two of the class trip...

2
00:00:13,941 --> 00:00:15,649
Group activities!

3
00:00:17,567 --> 00:00:20,317
Weren't the fall leaves
and the gardens pretty?

4
00:00:20,733 --> 00:00:22,692
The fall colors were nice...

5
00:00:22,693 --> 00:00:24,818
but the timing didn't work out, did it?

6
00:00:24,818 --> 00:00:26,651
What? T-Timing for what?

7
00:00:26,652 --> 00:00:28,569
Oh, you're pretending you don't know?

8
00:00:28,569 --> 00:00:31,194
We're going the same places as him, right?

9
00:00:31,195 --> 00:00:32,861
Oh, no, that's...

10
00:00:32,861 --> 00:00:36,445
It was just a "maybe we might
see each other."

11
00:00:36,737 --> 00:00:40,446
Being able to take beautiful photos
is enough to make me than happy.

12
00:00:40,905 --> 00:00:43,697
Truthfully, I was just a little hopeful.

13
00:00:44,905 --> 00:00:48,363
You know, instead of going "it would be
nice if we saw each other,"

14
00:00:48,364 --> 00:00:50,948
you could just set a time
and place to meet.

15
00:00:50,948 --> 00:00:51,739
What?

16
00:00:52,490 --> 00:00:55,074
Be alone with him somewhere
other than school?

17
00:00:55,907 --> 00:00:57,449
I could never.

18
00:00:58,450 --> 00:01:02,616
Oh, but... Hon-chan, leaving you
alone so suddenly would be...

19
00:01:04,075 --> 00:01:07,741
Huh? That's your reason? Really?

20
00:01:07,742 --> 00:01:11,617
I'm sorry. That was an underhanded excuse.

21
00:01:11,617 --> 00:01:13,076
All right. You're forgiven.

22
00:01:13,077 --> 00:01:16,493
I hate people who are evasive about
their true feelings, you know?

23
00:01:16,493 --> 00:01:18,618
I'm so sorry.

24
00:01:19,077 --> 00:01:22,035
Hey, girls! What are
you two talking about?

25
00:01:22,036 --> 00:01:23,161
Nothing!

26
00:01:23,161 --> 00:01:24,911
Huh? She lied.

27
00:01:38,496 --> 00:01:43,288
YOU AND I ARE POLAR OPPOSITES

28
00:02:59,049 --> 00:03:01,299
LOVE FORTUNE TELLING STONE

29
00:03:01,300 --> 00:03:03,883
The stones say if your love is real!

30
00:03:03,883 --> 00:03:04,925
My, how lovely.

31
00:03:04,925 --> 00:03:08,633
If you close your eyes and manage
to walk from one stone to the other,

32
00:03:08,634 --> 00:03:10,593
your love will be fulfilled!

33
00:03:10,594 --> 00:03:12,052
What?

34
00:03:12,427 --> 00:03:14,802
Still, it'd be too cringe to do, right?

35
00:03:14,803 --> 00:03:16,303
Me, me! I'll do it!

36
00:03:16,303 --> 00:03:17,053
Wow.

37
00:03:21,888 --> 00:03:23,722
You can do it, Yamada Man!

38
00:03:23,722 --> 00:03:25,388
Go! Go!

39
00:03:25,389 --> 00:03:27,931
- Yamada Man!
- Yamada's doing it.

40
00:03:28,348 --> 00:03:29,389
Right!

41
00:03:29,390 --> 00:03:30,515
Left!

42
00:03:30,515 --> 00:03:31,432
Reft!

43
00:03:31,432 --> 00:03:32,307
Which way?!

44
00:03:34,183 --> 00:03:35,225
Nice fight!

45
00:03:36,142 --> 00:03:37,851
I'm happy your love will work out.

46
00:03:38,476 --> 00:03:39,934
Morimo!

47
00:03:39,935 --> 00:03:42,268
What are you doing?
Don't get in the way!

48
00:03:42,269 --> 00:03:43,186
No, no.

49
00:03:43,186 --> 00:03:47,103
I'm way bigger than the stone, so the
effectiveness should be greater.

50
00:03:47,104 --> 00:03:48,312
What logic is that?

51
00:03:53,690 --> 00:03:56,690
Hey! I see a bunch of
our uniforms over there.

52
00:03:58,191 --> 00:03:59,858
Is that group 7?

53
00:04:00,734 --> 00:04:01,900
Try talking to him.

54
00:04:01,901 --> 00:04:02,735
What?

55
00:04:02,735 --> 00:04:05,318
No, he's with his friends.

56
00:04:05,319 --> 00:04:07,361
I might be interrupting.

57
00:04:07,362 --> 00:04:12,070
Well, if you're all right with that,
then I guess it's fine, but...

58
00:04:12,405 --> 00:04:14,572
Okay! Look over here!

59
00:04:14,573 --> 00:04:16,156
Stop that, Tani. Smile!

60
00:04:16,157 --> 00:04:18,407
Why make a face
like that for the camera?

61
00:04:18,408 --> 00:04:20,700
Come on! Look this way! Smile! Smile!

62
00:04:20,701 --> 00:04:21,784
Are we little kids?

63
00:04:21,785 --> 00:04:23,744
Suzuki, your face is tense.

64
00:04:23,745 --> 00:04:25,411
Suzuki! Your face is weird!

65
00:04:25,411 --> 00:04:26,703
My face is weird?!

66
00:04:26,954 --> 00:04:28,454
Hurry up and take it.

67
00:04:29,247 --> 00:04:30,413
Your feelings showed!

68
00:04:30,414 --> 00:04:31,998
Oh! Looking good!

69
00:04:32,915 --> 00:04:36,457
Going on your class trip with
a girlfriend must be nice, right?

70
00:04:36,459 --> 00:04:38,501
Sure.

71
00:04:38,502 --> 00:04:42,460
Even if I had one, I'd never
want to be that open about it.

72
00:04:42,713 --> 00:04:43,838
LOVE

73
00:04:43,838 --> 00:04:47,005
I just bought an charm,
so I have high hopes for future me!

74
00:04:47,007 --> 00:04:48,507
Oh! Hey, that's no fair!

75
00:04:48,508 --> 00:04:49,966
And after you got in my way!

76
00:04:49,967 --> 00:04:52,717
I wonder if there's a charm that—

77
00:04:52,719 --> 00:04:54,011
Yamada-kun.

78
00:04:58,680 --> 00:05:03,139
Oh, um, I'm sorry for interrupting
so suddenly. I saw you, so...

79
00:05:06,477 --> 00:05:08,477
GIGGLE GIGGLE

80
00:05:08,479 --> 00:05:12,479
I... thought I'd try
speaking to you. That's all.

81
00:05:15,066 --> 00:05:16,108
Voom!

82
00:05:16,109 --> 00:05:17,484
SUCKING THE CHARM POWER OUT
- Huh? What's all this?

83
00:05:18,111 --> 00:05:21,069
Oh! It's Nissan!
Let's get a photo together!

84
00:05:23,990 --> 00:05:26,032
It's a nice view, isn't it?

85
00:05:26,034 --> 00:05:27,450
What brought that on?

86
00:05:32,789 --> 00:05:33,789
Oh.

87
00:05:33,790 --> 00:05:36,540
Yamada-kun sent the
pictures from earlier.

88
00:05:37,459 --> 00:05:40,418
Wow. So many photos of
a bizarre group of people.

89
00:05:40,420 --> 00:05:42,086
You're right.

90
00:05:42,088 --> 00:05:45,880
If not for the class trip energy,
we probably wouldn't have taken these.

91
00:05:50,887 --> 00:05:52,429
Honestly, you had the chance.

92
00:05:52,431 --> 00:05:54,222
You should've posed together.

93
00:05:54,223 --> 00:05:54,890
What?

94
00:05:54,891 --> 00:05:57,308
Could we take one with just us two?

95
00:05:59,228 --> 00:06:01,937
With all those people
around, I just couldn't!

96
00:06:02,190 --> 00:06:06,190
Just going up and talking to him used up
all my emotional strength for today.

97
00:06:06,193 --> 00:06:08,318
INCREDIBLE, NISSHI!
- You did work hard for that.

98
00:06:08,821 --> 00:06:09,946
And actually...

99
00:06:10,238 --> 00:06:12,738
Yamada's got problems
without including me.

100
00:06:12,741 --> 00:06:14,908
He should've texted Nisshi privately.

101
00:06:14,910 --> 00:06:16,035
Moron. Incompetent.

102
00:06:16,036 --> 00:06:17,661
Wasn't this a chance to contact her?

103
00:06:19,247 --> 00:06:22,372
Oh, he texted again.
I wonder if it's a photo.

104
00:06:27,215 --> 00:06:28,715
What kind of photo is it?

105
00:06:28,716 --> 00:06:31,216
YAMADA
UNREAD MESSAGES BELOW
- CAN YOU LEAVE YOUR ROOM RIGHT NOW?

106
00:06:31,510 --> 00:06:35,260
What? He...
He's asking me directly. Wait.

107
00:06:35,264 --> 00:06:37,723
When is "right now"? What do I do?

108
00:06:40,062 --> 00:06:41,479
Go, Nisshi.

109
00:06:41,480 --> 00:06:44,188
What? But, Hon-chan,
I'd be leaving you alone.

110
00:06:44,191 --> 00:06:47,441
There's a livestream I want to watch,
so I won't be bothered.

111
00:06:47,445 --> 00:06:48,487
Oh, but...

112
00:06:50,366 --> 00:06:53,366
I'M IN THE LOBBY,
IN A PLACE WITH LOTS OF CHAIRS.

113
00:06:53,703 --> 00:06:57,328
People are wandering around the
hotel a lot more than I thought.

114
00:06:58,917 --> 00:07:00,417
There's Yamada-kun.

115
00:07:01,754 --> 00:07:04,254
Oh, some girls
I don't know have arrived.

116
00:07:05,384 --> 00:07:10,217
Wait. Does this mean that it's possible
I wasn't the only one he called out here?

117
00:07:11,224 --> 00:07:12,932
Oh, they left.

118
00:07:13,352 --> 00:07:14,894
But now here's someone else.

119
00:07:15,730 --> 00:07:18,647
I've only seen
that greeting done overseas.

120
00:07:19,026 --> 00:07:23,276
Actually, I feel like
Yamada-kun is with girls a lot.

121
00:07:24,033 --> 00:07:24,949
What's this?

122
00:07:25,868 --> 00:07:30,160
For some reason, I've naturally thought of
all of Yamada-kun's actions toward me

123
00:07:30,166 --> 00:07:34,416
as signs of some kind of affection,
and it turned my thinking into a mess.

124
00:07:34,755 --> 00:07:38,963
But what if this is all an
embarrassing misunderstanding?

125
00:07:38,969 --> 00:07:43,636
Like, for me this is something that never
happens, but for Yamada-kun it's normal?

126
00:07:43,643 --> 00:07:48,851
What do I do? I have so little experience
that I never even thought to question it!

127
00:07:48,858 --> 00:07:49,692
Hey.

128
00:07:49,693 --> 00:07:51,318
You should say hi.

129
00:07:53,532 --> 00:07:55,032
Oh, um...

130
00:07:55,034 --> 00:07:58,451
It's just... you were
with other people, so...

131
00:07:58,456 --> 00:08:00,706
Oh. You don't want
other people to see you?

132
00:08:00,710 --> 00:08:02,793
It's, um...

133
00:08:03,254 --> 00:08:05,796
This is bad.
My self-conscious side is showing.

134
00:08:05,800 --> 00:08:07,717
Yeah, you have a point.

135
00:08:08,512 --> 00:08:10,096
Right now, I hate the idea, too.

136
00:08:10,933 --> 00:08:12,225
Right now?

137
00:08:12,227 --> 00:08:13,810
All right.

138
00:08:14,105 --> 00:08:16,605
Let's go and talk quietly
by ourselves.

139
00:08:22,284 --> 00:08:25,784
All the awful imaginings
that were jumbled up in my head

140
00:08:25,789 --> 00:08:28,081
were blown away in an instant.

141
00:08:35,263 --> 00:08:39,679
Yamada-kun's words and actions
are always so straightforward.

142
00:08:42,776 --> 00:08:45,359
Nishi-san, was this cat around
when you went by?

143
00:08:45,363 --> 00:08:47,113
What? No.

144
00:08:47,116 --> 00:08:48,158
It's so cute!

145
00:08:48,160 --> 00:08:50,951
Oh! This is Taira,
the guy I was telling you about...

146
00:08:50,955 --> 00:08:53,622
Oh, I think I've seen him before.

147
00:08:53,627 --> 00:08:55,252
And this is Azuma...

148
00:08:55,254 --> 00:08:56,671
A pretty older sister.

149
00:08:56,674 --> 00:08:58,174
And this bald giant is Morimo.

150
00:08:58,176 --> 00:08:59,134
*MORIMOTO
- Morimo?

151
00:09:00,555 --> 00:09:01,263
TAIRA: OUR TURN FOR THE BATH IS COMING UP
- Oh.

152
00:09:02,183 --> 00:09:03,849
I've gotta get back.

153
00:09:03,852 --> 00:09:05,727
Y-Yes, me too.

154
00:09:09,654 --> 00:09:10,696
So, um...

155
00:09:12,200 --> 00:09:13,866
Want to go hang out somewhere?

156
00:09:13,869 --> 00:09:15,453
After the class trip.

157
00:09:17,460 --> 00:09:20,668
Like, maybe somewhere we
won't run into anyone from school.

158
00:09:20,673 --> 00:09:21,965
Anywhere is good.

159
00:09:22,301 --> 00:09:23,426
Just the two of us.

160
00:09:25,890 --> 00:09:26,974
Yes.

161
00:09:27,853 --> 00:09:29,311
What do I do?

162
00:09:36,326 --> 00:09:40,909
WHY ME? WHAT SHOULD I ACCEPT? REALLY?
- Thinking about Yamada-kun's feelings,
there's so much I don't understand.

163
00:09:42,003 --> 00:09:45,461
I hate people who are evasive about
their true feelings, you know?

164
00:09:46,469 --> 00:09:48,969
These feelings of mine...

165
00:09:50,727 --> 00:09:52,685
I can't explain them away anymore.

166
00:09:54,442 --> 00:09:55,609
I love him.

167
00:09:57,697 --> 00:09:59,781
MEANWHILE

168
00:09:59,785 --> 00:10:01,618
Nothing beats my bias.

169
00:10:04,001 --> 00:10:07,751
Back in middle school,
I couldn't say I didn't want to go,

170
00:10:07,758 --> 00:10:09,091
so I reluctantly went,

171
00:10:09,093 --> 00:10:12,635
thinking "I want to hurry up and
go home" as I endured my class trip.

172
00:10:14,603 --> 00:10:16,603
But now...

173
00:10:26,918 --> 00:10:28,626
to be honest...

174
00:10:29,130 --> 00:10:31,839
I'm having fun. A lot of fun.

175
00:10:32,721 --> 00:10:34,971
Class trip, day three!

176
00:10:34,975 --> 00:10:36,725
Class activities!

177
00:10:41,237 --> 00:10:44,028
Teacher! Is it okay for me
to get some ice cream?

178
00:10:44,033 --> 00:10:45,283
How casual are you?

179
00:10:45,285 --> 00:10:46,577
Huh? Sure.

180
00:10:46,580 --> 00:10:47,788
It's fine?

181
00:10:48,082 --> 00:10:50,499
I mean, we got around to everything fast.

182
00:10:50,504 --> 00:10:51,587
Right?

183
00:10:51,589 --> 00:10:54,172
Before I knew it, we had
left the other classes behind!

184
00:10:54,720 --> 00:10:57,137
As long as you make it back
before the bus leaves,

185
00:10:57,141 --> 00:10:58,932
you can wander around wherever.

186
00:10:58,935 --> 00:11:00,435
Yeah!

187
00:11:00,438 --> 00:11:01,730
Yay!

188
00:11:01,733 --> 00:11:02,775
Ya—

189
00:11:04,571 --> 00:11:05,488
What?

190
00:11:05,489 --> 00:11:07,031
Oh, nothing.

191
00:11:07,034 --> 00:11:08,450
Stop looking at me like that.

192
00:11:11,000 --> 00:11:13,333
After breaking free of my hometown,

193
00:11:13,337 --> 00:11:15,962
I may accidentally verge
on getting overly excited,

194
00:11:16,259 --> 00:11:19,759
but the moment I see myself
like that, my limiter kicks in.

195
00:11:19,766 --> 00:11:22,058
AZUMA KNOWS THE OLD ME.
BACK THEN, I WAS LOW-LEVEL, THOUGH.
- Especially when I'm with Azuma.

196
00:11:22,062 --> 00:11:24,062
I DON'T WANT HER THINKING I'M LIVING IT UP
IN THIS NEW ENVIRONMENT.
- All these concerns mix together into...

197
00:11:25,067 --> 00:11:27,983
An incomplete sense of
self-consciousness and inferiority.

198
00:11:27,988 --> 00:11:29,822
Huh? Where'd that come from?

199
00:11:30,785 --> 00:11:33,743
Oh! Hey, I want to buy some deer senbei!

200
00:11:34,083 --> 00:11:35,916
There's ten in a packet. Shall we share?

201
00:11:35,920 --> 00:11:36,837
Oh, my!

202
00:11:37,673 --> 00:11:38,590
What?

203
00:11:38,591 --> 00:11:39,674
Nothing.

204
00:11:39,676 --> 00:11:42,551
Taira, wanna go halfsies with me?

205
00:11:42,556 --> 00:11:43,514
Okay.

206
00:11:46,021 --> 00:11:49,105
Wow! They're already standing by!

207
00:11:49,110 --> 00:11:50,818
They're used to getting fed.

208
00:11:52,407 --> 00:11:53,782
They're really rushing over!

209
00:11:54,369 --> 00:11:56,785
Wait! This is pretty scary!

210
00:11:57,040 --> 00:11:59,665
Whoa! Drool! Calm down!

211
00:11:59,669 --> 00:12:01,211
Stay! Stay! Time out! Stay!

212
00:12:01,214 --> 00:12:02,672
Stay! Wait! Stay!

213
00:12:02,925 --> 00:12:05,884
Yamada sure is talking
to those deer a lot.

214
00:12:05,889 --> 00:12:07,180
Listen to this!

215
00:12:07,182 --> 00:12:11,057
Those deer ate everything they could
eat in a flash and then they all left!

216
00:12:11,064 --> 00:12:13,439
Doesn't look like that's happening there.

217
00:12:13,818 --> 00:12:15,068
I don't have any more!

218
00:12:15,363 --> 00:12:17,488
Taira's so popular with the deer.

219
00:12:18,827 --> 00:12:21,327
Hey! Stop laughing and help me!

220
00:12:28,927 --> 00:12:29,760
Huh?

221
00:12:33,559 --> 00:12:38,309
BUS TOUR STYLE
- And now, if I could have your attention
for the return trip!

222
00:12:38,859 --> 00:12:41,359
If you think we're gonna
keep this party going,

223
00:12:41,363 --> 00:12:42,863
throw your hands in the air!

224
00:12:42,865 --> 00:12:44,532
Yay!

225
00:12:44,534 --> 00:12:46,742
Don't give a mid-concert talk.

226
00:12:46,996 --> 00:12:50,746
In the front row! Tani-kun,
how's your car sickness?

227
00:12:51,753 --> 00:12:54,545
Stop sliding personal info into your talk.

228
00:12:54,549 --> 00:12:55,382
Taira.

229
00:12:55,384 --> 00:12:56,259
Huh?

230
00:12:56,594 --> 00:12:57,510
Over here.

231
00:12:58,013 --> 00:13:02,013
YAMADA: HELPING WITH THE TALK,
TANI: MOVED, SUZUKI: GIVING THE TALK
- And now, I'd like to do a quiz!

232
00:13:02,018 --> 00:13:03,477
Here's question 1!

233
00:13:03,813 --> 00:13:05,230
What two animals are hidden
in the Japanese name for April 1st?

234
00:13:05,232 --> 00:13:08,023
I bought lots of snacks,
so let's eat some.

235
00:13:08,444 --> 00:13:09,694
That's way too many.

236
00:13:10,030 --> 00:13:14,072
- Those remind me of an elementary school
field trip. So nostalgic.
- Anyone know the answer?

237
00:13:14,077 --> 00:13:15,744
- Then it goes to you, Yamada!
- Nabe recommended them.

238
00:13:15,747 --> 00:13:18,538
- No clue!
- Don't be so happy about it!
- You don't like Nabe-chan's picks, Taira?

239
00:13:18,541 --> 00:13:20,916
- The answer is, you take
the "itachi" from "shigatsu tsuitachi,"
- I wasn't complaining. Now sit properly.

240
00:13:21,170 --> 00:13:24,420
- Oh! Taira, this one has a lucky piece.
- and since that date is also referred to
as "watanuki," the answer is two tanuki!

241
00:13:24,717 --> 00:13:25,717
I'll give you one.

242
00:13:25,718 --> 00:13:27,218
Tell me if you win, okay?

243
00:13:27,470 --> 00:13:28,428
Wow.

244
00:13:29,305 --> 00:13:31,430
You didn't understand it at all, did you?

245
00:13:33,520 --> 00:13:34,478
Wow, that's sour.

246
00:13:34,479 --> 00:13:36,021
- Your reaction is way too small.
- And now for question 3!

247
00:13:36,023 --> 00:13:39,189
Isn't this normal? You expect weird stuff.
- What kind of bird do you get
when you have nine all together?

248
00:13:43,031 --> 00:13:43,781
Over here!

249
00:13:43,782 --> 00:13:46,823
Oh! Zuma-chan! Having an active
participant is so helpful!

250
00:13:46,827 --> 00:13:48,036
A nine-ah bird!

251
00:13:48,037 --> 00:13:49,495
Incorrect! Too bad!

252
00:13:49,497 --> 00:13:50,914
And she got it wrong?

253
00:13:51,291 --> 00:13:54,874
- What? But I was so sure it was right.
- That was a tough one.
The correct answer is... pigeon!

254
00:13:54,878 --> 00:13:56,253
Huh? Why a pigeon?

255
00:13:56,964 --> 00:13:59,506
- Pigeon is written with kanji
for "nine" and "bird."
- You're weirded out because I was wrong?

256
00:13:59,508 --> 00:14:00,800
- Yamada, can you write
the kanji for pigeon?
- Huh? No.

257
00:14:01,093 --> 00:14:05,677
- It's just... Was Azuma always like this?
- Pretty much no.
- Are you gonna be okay?

258
00:14:09,852 --> 00:14:12,311
Tani, are you okay?

259
00:14:12,314 --> 00:14:15,022
Dinner tonight is all-you-can-eat!
Can you handle it?

260
00:14:15,025 --> 00:14:16,400
Meat! Meat! Meat!

261
00:14:16,859 --> 00:14:18,984
Don't make him imagine that right now!

262
00:14:18,986 --> 00:14:21,820
I want to feel the wind
for a while. Go on ahead.

263
00:14:21,823 --> 00:14:23,448
Take care!

264
00:14:23,450 --> 00:14:25,783
If you don't know
where to go, just call me!

265
00:14:25,785 --> 00:14:26,827
Thank you.

266
00:14:27,161 --> 00:14:30,328
And of course,
this is the one time I'm out of tea.

267
00:14:30,331 --> 00:14:32,831
It's all right. Thank you.

268
00:14:37,087 --> 00:14:39,420
What? You're having
a cola before a buffet?

269
00:14:41,423 --> 00:14:43,715
There's no need to be that shocked.

270
00:14:44,093 --> 00:14:49,593
No, it's just... I've heard that
cola works for car sickness.

271
00:14:49,597 --> 00:14:51,680
That's so kind of you!

272
00:14:51,682 --> 00:14:53,640
Stop doing stuff like that!

273
00:14:54,767 --> 00:14:57,726
Tani-kun, do you usually get carsick?

274
00:14:57,728 --> 00:15:00,853
No, not usually. Just for some reason...

275
00:15:01,146 --> 00:15:02,896
But I'm all right now.

276
00:15:02,898 --> 00:15:06,898
That's a relief. Maybe you weren't
feeling well to begin with?

277
00:15:06,900 --> 00:15:08,775
We still have tomorrow, too.

278
00:15:08,777 --> 00:15:10,152
I'm all right.

279
00:15:10,152 --> 00:15:13,861
In that case, it gets chilly at night,
so I'll head back to where everyone—

280
00:15:18,367 --> 00:15:20,908
Stay with me just a little longer?

281
00:15:23,703 --> 00:15:25,036
Okay.

282
00:15:41,379 --> 00:15:44,545
What was that?!
I regret ever worrying about him!

283
00:15:47,506 --> 00:15:51,506
That was insane! They're totally living
the springtime of youth! I was shocked!

284
00:15:52,008 --> 00:15:53,841
I saw something great.
That was fun!

285
00:15:53,842 --> 00:15:56,634
It was not good and it was not fun!

286
00:15:56,635 --> 00:15:59,801
Oh, I don't care anymore.
I'll drink this myself.

287
00:16:02,720 --> 00:16:05,512
Argh! Seriously?!

288
00:16:07,013 --> 00:16:09,804
Wait! I can't! My stomach hurts!

289
00:16:09,805 --> 00:16:11,930
Don't laugh at other people's misfortune!

290
00:16:11,931 --> 00:16:14,015
But this is something you laugh at.

291
00:16:20,767 --> 00:16:24,183
Somehow, Azuma, you're more...

292
00:16:25,393 --> 00:16:27,268
classmate-like than I thought.

293
00:16:33,770 --> 00:16:35,770
Huh? Of course I am.

294
00:16:37,271 --> 00:16:38,771
What?

295
00:16:38,771 --> 00:16:40,979
We always talk casually with each other.

296
00:16:40,979 --> 00:16:43,937
And we were in the same class
together last year, right?

297
00:16:43,938 --> 00:16:44,813
What?

298
00:16:44,813 --> 00:16:48,480
Yeah, I mean... That's true, but...

299
00:16:49,273 --> 00:16:51,856
"You've changed somehow"
is what I wanted to, uh...

300
00:16:51,856 --> 00:16:55,106
But what good does saying that do?
That's creepy!

301
00:16:56,273 --> 00:16:56,981
What?

302
00:16:56,981 --> 00:16:58,606
What was that just now?

303
00:16:58,607 --> 00:16:59,315
It's not fair!

304
00:16:59,315 --> 00:17:00,524
It was adorable!

305
00:17:01,149 --> 00:17:03,524
FEVERISH
RECOVERED A WHILE AGO

306
00:17:03,857 --> 00:17:06,024
Class trip, the final day!

307
00:17:06,024 --> 00:17:08,149
Free time!

308
00:17:12,191 --> 00:17:13,816
Where should we go first?

309
00:17:13,816 --> 00:17:16,400
We don't have much time, though.

310
00:17:16,400 --> 00:17:17,941
Aren't you going somewhere else?

311
00:17:17,941 --> 00:17:19,775
That was blunt.

312
00:17:19,775 --> 00:17:21,858
Well, enjoy your date.

313
00:17:21,858 --> 00:17:24,150
If we run into you,
we'll pretend we didn't.

314
00:17:24,150 --> 00:17:26,400
It's fine. You don't have to go that far.

315
00:17:26,400 --> 00:17:30,233
Couples tend to argue on
amusement park dates, so be careful.

316
00:17:30,233 --> 00:17:32,400
There you go,
saying stuff like that again.

317
00:17:32,400 --> 00:17:36,441
When a guy has a bad attitude
waiting in lines or driving,

318
00:17:36,441 --> 00:17:38,608
you should assume
that's their true nature.

319
00:17:38,608 --> 00:17:40,400
That's not from experience, is it?

320
00:17:42,316 --> 00:17:43,858
Where do you want to start?

321
00:17:43,858 --> 00:17:46,400
Oh! There's a spot
I want to stop by first!

322
00:17:46,400 --> 00:17:49,150
This is it! A popcorn case!

323
00:17:49,400 --> 00:17:51,775
I wanted to wear this
and walk around!

324
00:17:51,775 --> 00:17:52,775
Isn't it adorable?

325
00:17:53,066 --> 00:17:54,150
Adora...

326
00:17:57,441 --> 00:17:58,733
It seems like your thing.

327
00:17:59,566 --> 00:18:02,316
I want to look at the hats
and headbands and stuff, too!

328
00:18:02,650 --> 00:18:05,816
This is so exciting!

329
00:18:06,150 --> 00:18:07,066
Huh?

330
00:18:11,566 --> 00:18:13,733
Tani-kun, I wasn't expecting that choice.

331
00:18:13,733 --> 00:18:14,608
This...

332
00:18:15,316 --> 00:18:16,608
seems like you'd wear it.

333
00:18:17,775 --> 00:18:19,483
I'd wear it?

334
00:18:20,150 --> 00:18:21,733
You mean it'd look nice on me?

335
00:18:21,733 --> 00:18:22,441
Yeah.

336
00:18:22,441 --> 00:18:23,566
Oh, my!

337
00:18:23,941 --> 00:18:27,191
In that case, which of these
would look good on Tani-kun?

338
00:18:27,191 --> 00:18:27,941
What?

339
00:18:27,941 --> 00:18:29,233
I'm okay without one.

340
00:18:29,233 --> 00:18:30,066
Huh?

341
00:18:30,358 --> 00:18:32,525
O-Oh, really?

342
00:18:33,316 --> 00:18:36,733
That was close! I was getting
all excited on my own again.

343
00:18:36,733 --> 00:18:37,900
If I don't get a grip,

344
00:18:37,900 --> 00:18:41,525
he'll end up next to an avatar
loaded up with paid gacha pulls.

345
00:18:42,192 --> 00:18:47,317
But, I was sort of hoping to do casually
matching headbands or something.

346
00:18:47,651 --> 00:18:49,942
I guess he's not that type.

347
00:18:49,942 --> 00:18:50,651
Oh.

348
00:18:51,692 --> 00:18:53,442
Do you want to buy matching ones?

349
00:18:53,442 --> 00:18:56,109
Sort of... like we did before.

350
00:18:57,068 --> 00:18:57,818
Yeah!

351
00:19:01,943 --> 00:19:05,152
Merch like this is okay,
but headbands are a no-go?

352
00:19:05,152 --> 00:19:08,943
It's just... I can't imagine myself
wearing something like that.

353
00:19:09,236 --> 00:19:12,694
They look good on you,
but I'd look weird, wouldn't I?

354
00:19:12,695 --> 00:19:14,695
What? You wouldn't look weird!

355
00:19:14,987 --> 00:19:18,654
Actually, in places like this,
you should be weird.

356
00:19:18,655 --> 00:19:20,030
You'll regret not going nuts.

357
00:19:20,030 --> 00:19:20,946
Right.

358
00:19:20,946 --> 00:19:24,280
Let's break out of that
shell of yours, Yuusuke-san!

359
00:19:24,281 --> 00:19:25,489
Um...

360
00:19:26,031 --> 00:19:27,489
You don't like the idea!

361
00:19:27,782 --> 00:19:29,740
It's fine! No need to force yourself!

362
00:19:34,574 --> 00:19:36,449
Do you want some? Go ahead.

363
00:19:36,450 --> 00:19:37,367
Thanks.

364
00:19:43,077 --> 00:19:46,577
For some reason, it's starting
to look cuter and cuter to me.

365
00:19:46,579 --> 00:19:48,829
So it wasn't cute to you before?

366
00:20:01,335 --> 00:20:03,044
This is so much fun!

367
00:20:04,879 --> 00:20:10,587
Nabe and the others told me not to argue
because wait times are so long,

368
00:20:10,882 --> 00:20:13,299
but not having fun is harder, right?

369
00:20:13,301 --> 00:20:13,926
NEEDLESS WORRY OF THE YEAR

370
00:20:14,843 --> 00:20:16,010
Yeah, that's true.

371
00:20:16,886 --> 00:20:20,053
But, time-wise, we might not
be able to do anything else.

372
00:20:20,055 --> 00:20:21,888
Really? Already?

373
00:20:24,184 --> 00:20:25,975
I just got a text from Azu.

374
00:20:27,144 --> 00:20:29,352
It looks like everyone else
is together.

375
00:20:29,646 --> 00:20:32,063
I guess we should go and join them!

376
00:20:33,191 --> 00:20:36,899
We have to get ready to
go home already? That's so sad!

377
00:20:40,823 --> 00:20:41,781
Miyu...

378
00:20:48,163 --> 00:20:49,080
...chan.

379
00:20:49,414 --> 00:20:51,622
A BELATED "-CHAN"...

380
00:20:52,376 --> 00:20:53,751
What's wrong?

381
00:20:54,253 --> 00:20:55,670
Um...

382
00:20:56,923 --> 00:20:59,965
Let's... take the long way there.

383
00:21:02,722 --> 00:21:06,722
Y-Yuusuke-kun... hold on.

384
00:21:07,103 --> 00:21:11,019
Today, you're...
Actually, yesterday, too...

385
00:21:11,024 --> 00:21:13,399
No, actually, before that, too...

386
00:21:14,321 --> 00:21:15,904
Are you trying to kill me?

387
00:21:15,906 --> 00:21:16,781
What?

388
00:21:18,160 --> 00:21:21,494
I don't know why. I...

389
00:21:22,250 --> 00:21:24,708
Maybe I've gone a little weird.

390
00:21:25,839 --> 00:21:27,589
What kind of laugh was that?

391
00:21:32,934 --> 00:21:34,559
Boys, that's crazy!

392
00:21:34,562 --> 00:21:36,021
Why are you all wearing those?

393
00:21:36,024 --> 00:21:37,274
How'd it start?

394
00:21:37,276 --> 00:21:37,984
For the looks.

395
00:21:38,319 --> 00:21:40,736
The crew members asked
about it, right?

396
00:21:40,741 --> 00:21:43,574
I didn't realize that people
greeted each other that much.

397
00:21:44,123 --> 00:21:46,081
STARE...

398
00:21:54,269 --> 00:21:55,602
Taira-kun...

399
00:21:55,602 --> 00:21:58,977
YOU'RE WEARING ONE...
- What? Why are you only
giving me that reaction?

400
00:22:00,227 --> 00:22:02,894
Hey! Let's all take
a group picture together!

401
00:22:02,894 --> 00:22:04,894
Yay!

402
00:22:06,727 --> 00:22:10,227
Are you thinking you should've
just gone all the way insane?

403
00:22:10,227 --> 00:22:11,436
No.

404
00:22:11,436 --> 00:22:13,269
Okay! I'm taking it now.

405
00:22:13,269 --> 00:22:14,311
Just a little.

406
00:22:15,394 --> 00:22:16,852
In that case...

407
00:22:18,186 --> 00:22:19,769
We'll have to come back, right?

408
00:22:20,227 --> 00:22:21,061
Yeah.
